A majority of Icelanders oppose a
decision by the legislature to indict former Prime Minister Geir Haarde for criminal negligence leading up to the islandâ€™s
economic collapse, a MMR  poll showed .  The poll found 65.7 percent of voters were opposed to the
move, while 34.3 percent were in favor.  MMR polled 867 people June 9 through June 15. Of those
polled, 83.6 percent responded. No margin of error was provided.  To contact the reporter on this story:
